name: Tykeson Hall OSU Cascades
directions: Go through the door nearest the parking lot, the building has big letters on it labeling it 'Tykeson Hall.' You'll see a sign with a "woman" figure, a "man" figure and the accessibility symbol. Take a right into this hall. The All Gender bathroom is the first door on the right. Use the card to unlock the door, and press the red button inside to lock the door.
comment: You may have to be a student, but I'm not certain. As long as you're not too sketchy you should be fine.

comment: Official policy is that the whole store including bathrooms is open to anyone, paying customer or not, and bathrooms were consciously de-gendered a few years ago. Many LGBT staff members, this is the unofficial local refuge.

name: Cranston Branch YMCA
directions: On the lower level, with the other changing rooms.
comment: If you have a YMCA membership, you can use the family changing rooms here. Each individual stall has a shower, a toilet, and a changing table. You have to be a Y member, though.

name: Brydges Street Merchant Market
directions: Go into the building and it's to the right where all the antique daltons and glass ware are, if you have trouble, just ask the front desk.
comment: This is a large 2 stall washroom with an old style urinal and a sink but theirs a sign on the door that says lock the whole washroom behind you, so you have a few options all to yourself or if you and a friend have to both go, you'll each have privacy. Don't touch the lights or fan, just leave them be. unfortunately their's no accessibility stall and as it's an older place, is not super wheel chair accessible to begin with. They have body sprays and room sprays if your anxious about that sort of thing and get the good soaps from the body shop, but just be aware if your allergic to scents.  Do take a lap around the mall as its pretty cool place and they got all sorts of wild and cool stuff. Just don't use the bathroom and leave as they have a hard time selling stuff, but they won't bother you unless you ask for help. so at least marvel at the cool stuff around you before you leave as that would be a waste.

name: Natalie Keister
directions: South Hill Community Park - Corner of (144th St E. &  86th Ave E.
comment: Bathrooms are open during daylight hours.

comment: You'll have to get past the turnstiles, if you aren't a member you can ask the front desk to open the handicap gate. There are two non-gendered single stall rooms

name: Olean YMCA
